Class Squirrel

java.lang.Object
Squirrel
public class Squirrel
extends java.lang.Object
This class reprsents a Squirrel piece on the board game "Cache Noisette!".

    • Squirrel

      public Squirrel​(Picture head, Picture tail, int headX, int headY, int tailX, int tailY, java.lang.String type, java.lang.String headType)
      Constructor that creates a 2 tile Squirrel with the given parameters.
      Parameters:
      head - the picture of the head of the Squirrel.
      tail - the picture of the tail of the Squirrel.
      headX - the x coordinates of the head of the Squirrel.
      headY - the y coordinates of the head of the Squirrel.
      tailX - the x coordinates of the tail of the Squirrel.
      tailY - the y coordinates of the tail of the Squirrel.
      type - a way to differentiate a Squirrel from one another (red/grey/brown/black).
      headType - a way to differentiate a nutHead from a simple head.

    • Squirrel

      public Squirrel​(Picture head, Picture tail, Picture flower, int headX, int headY, int tailX, int tailY, int flowerX, int flowerY, java.lang.String type, java.lang.String headType)
      Constructor that creates a 3 tile Squirrel with the given parameters.
      Parameters:

      tail - the picture of the tail of the Squirrel.

      tailX - the x coordinates of the tail of the Squirrel.
      tailY - the y coordinates of the tail of the Squirrel.
      flowerX - the x coordinates of the flower of the Squirrel.
      flowerY - the y coordinates of the flower of the Squirrel.
      type - a way to differentiate a Squirrel from one another (red/grey/brown/black).
      headType - a way to differentiate a nutHead from a simple head.
